ecoming president and chief operating officer as part of the deal allergan shareholders would receive  shares of the company with pfizer shareholders receiving one the terms proposed that the merged company would maintain allergans irish domicile resulting in the new company being subject to corporation tax at the irish rate of considerably lower than the  rate that pfizer paid at the time the deal was to constitute a reverse merger whereby allergan acquired pfizer with the new company then changing its name to pfizer plc the deal was expected to be completed in the second half of  subject to certain conditions us and eu approval approval from both sets of shareholders and the completion of allergans divestiture of its generics division to teva pharmaceuticals expected in the first quarter of  on april   pfizer and allergan announced they would be calling off the merger after the obama administration introduced new laws intended to limit corporate tax inversions the extent to which companies could move their headquarters overseas in order to reduce the amount of taxes they pay acquisition historyedit a full list of pfizers subsidiary holdings can be found here   illustration of the companys mergers acquisitions spinoffs and historical predecessors pfizer pfizer founded  as charles pfizer  company warner–lambert warner–lambert merged  william r warner founded  lambert pharmacal company parkedavis founded  acq  wilkinson sword acq  divested  agouron acq  pharmacia acq  pharmacia  upjohn merged  pharmacia ab merged  farmitalia carlo erba kabi pharmacia pharmacia aktiebolaget the upjohn company merged  monsanto merged  searle merged  monsanto company spun off  esperion therapeutics acq  sold  meridica acq  vicuron pharmaceuticals acq  idun acq  angiosyn acq  powermed acq  rinat acq  coley pharmaceutical group acq  covx acq  encysive pharmaceuticals inc acq  wyeth acq  american home products wyeth acq  chef boyardee sma corporation ayerst laboratories acq  fort dodge ser